text: Kintaqa is a genus of Thai and Malaysian cellar spiders first described by B. A. Huber, J. Eberle & D. Dimitrov in 2018. ==Species== it contains five species: *Kintaqa buatong (Huber, 2016) — Thailand *Kintaqa fuza (Yao & Li, 2017) — Thailand *Kintaqa mueangensis (Yao & Li, 2017) — Thailand *Kintaqa satun (Huber, 2011) — Thailand, Malaysia *Kintaqa schwendingeri (Huber, 2011) — Thailand ==References== ==External links== Category:Araneomorphae genera Category:Pholcidae
title: Kintaqa
